arch:property.oc:show_val: No material from the dry sieve. Sample 2 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. This is a fairly large sample with a middeny look. It is primarily composed of sheep-size animals, with all body parts represented although the toes are mostly digested. Ribs are present in higher proportions than usual, and there are even some vertebrae. Fairly high levels of digestion attest to the presence of dog feces, while two probably shed sheep/goat teeth suggest penning. There is a bit of bird, fish, and probably intrusive microfauna. While there is a goodly quantity of little crumbles, fragment size in general is relatively large. There is not a lot of coherence. This deposit seems to result from several activities. While some may be redeposited, it does not on the whole look very worn and reworked. We seem to have penning, butchery, post-consumption waste, and disposal of collected dog poop. A rib head with its unfused epiphysis still in articulation shows that some things went in and remained undisturbed. Last number = 104

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
